verses.verse: Praise <S%H1984><s%> <S%H8761><s%> ye the YY <S%H3050><s%>. Praise <S%H1984><s%> <S%H8761><s%> the YY <S%H3068><s%>, O my soul <S%H5315><s%>.
While I live <S%H2416><s%> will I praise <S%H1984><s%> <S%H8762><s%> the YY <S%H3068><s%>: I will sing praises <S%H2167><s%> <S%H8762><s%> unto my 'Elohim <S%H430><s%> while I have any being.
Put not your trust <S%H982><s%> <S%H8799><s%> in princes <S%H5081><s%>, nor in the son <S%H1121><s%> of man <S%H120><s%>, in whom there is no help <S%H8668><s%>.

His breath <S%H7307><s%> goeth forth <S%H3318><s%> <S%H8799><s%>, he returneth <S%H7725><s%> <S%H8799><s%> to his earth <S%H127><s%>; in that very day <S%H3117><s%> his thoughts <S%H6250><s%> perish <S%H6><s%> <S%H8804><s%>.
Happy <S%H835><s%> is he that hath the 'Elohim <S%H410><s%> of Ya`akov <S%H3290><s%> for his help <S%H5828><s%>, whose hope <S%H7664><s%> is in the YY <S%H3068><s%> his 'Elohim <S%H430><s%>:

Which made <S%H6213><s%> <S%H8802><s%> heaven <S%H8064><s%>, and earth <S%H776><s%>, the sea <S%H3220><s%>, and all that therein is: which keepeth <S%H8104><s%> <S%H8802><s%> truth <S%H571><s%> for ever <S%H5769><s%>:

Which executeth <S%H6213><s%> <S%H8802><s%> judgment <S%H4941><s%> for the oppressed <S%H6231><s%> <S%H8803><s%>: which giveth <S%H5414><s%> <S%H8802><s%> food <S%H3899><s%> to the hungry <S%H7457><s%>. The YY <S%H3068><s%> looseht <S%H5425><s%> <S%H8688><s%> the prisoners <S%H631><s%> <S%H8803><s%>:

The YY <S%H3068><s%> openeth <S%H6491><s%> <S%H8802><s%> the eyes of the blind <S%H5787><s%>: the YY <S%H3068><s%> raiseht <S%H2210><s%> <S%H8802><s%> them that are bowed down <S%H3721><s%> <S%H8803><s%>: the YY <S%H3068><s%> loveth <S%H157><s%> <S%H8802><s%> the righteous <S%H6662><s%>:

The YY <S%H3068><s%> preserveth <S%H8104><s%> <S%H8802><s%> the strangers <S%H1616><s%>; he relieveth <S%H5749><s%> <S%H8766><s%> the fatherless <S%H3490><s%> and widow <S%H490><s%>: but the way <S%H1870><s%> of the wicked <S%H7563><s%> he turneth upside down <S%H5791><s%> <S%H8762><s%>.

The YY <S%H3068><s%> shall reign <S%H4427><s%> <S%H8799><s%> for ever <S%H5769><s%>, even thy 'Elohim <S%H430><s%>, O TZiyon <S%H6726><s%>, unto all <S%H1755><s%> generations <S%H1755><s%>. Praise <S%H1984><s%> <S%H8761><s%> ye the YY <S%H3050><s%>.
